<div id="review_2901640987" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2901640987" />
    <a title="Kacey" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16238941-kacey"><img alt="Kacey" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2901640987?book_show_action=true">Jul 18, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kacey" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kacey" href="/user/show/16238941-kacey">Kacey</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16238941-kacey?shelf=childhood-favourites">childhood-favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16238941-kacey?shelf=books-i-own">books-i-own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16238941-kacey?shelf=read-in-2019">read-in-2019</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2901640987" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3462891524530440952">Whilst I&apos;ve put this in my Childhood Favourites folder, I never actually read it as a child, but I&apos;ve begun a project to read all the books in my childhood bookshelves...<br/><br/>It is important to note, this book has not aged well. When reading to a modem child, you would need to prepare a discussion afterwards about why we don&apos;t call people of colour &apos;savages&apos;, or talk to servants as though they were subhuman anymore. <br/><br/>That said, it is an innovative adventure story of its time, and would be an interesti</span>
  <span id="freeText3462891524530440952" style="display:none">Whilst I've put this in my Childhood Favourites folder, I never actually read it as a child, but I've begun a project to read all the books in my childhood bookshelves...<br /><br />It is important to note, this book has not aged well. When reading to a modem child, you would need to prepare a discussion afterwards about why we don't call people of colour 'savages', or talk to servants as though they were subhuman anymore. <br /><br />That said, it is an innovative adventure story of its time, and would be an interesting one to read with an older child, if only to talk about how children's books have changed over the last hundred-odd years!</span>
  <a data-text-id="3462891524530440952" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


